concept_explanation.n_plus_one:
**N+1 with @SchemaMapping:**

```java
// NAIVE (N+1 problem):
@SchemaMapping(typeName = "Product")
public List<Review> reviews(Product product) {
    // Called ONCE PER PRODUCT in the result!
    // 200 products → 200 separate DB calls
    return reviewRepository.findByProductId(product.getId());
}
```

concept_explanation.batch_mapping:
**@BatchMapping — the fix:**

```java
// BATCHED (N+1 solved):
@BatchMapping(typeName = "Product", field = "reviews")
public Map<Product, List<Review>> reviews(List<Product> products) {
    // Called ONCE with ALL products in the result!
    // Extract all IDs:
    List<String> productIds = products.stream()
        .map(Product::getId).toList();

    // ONE query for all reviews:
    List<Review> allReviews = reviewRepository
        .findByProductIdIn(productIds); // IN query

    // Group by product:
    Map<String, List<Review>> byProductId = allReviews.stream()
        .collect(Collectors.groupingBy(Review::getProductId));

    // Return Map<Product, List<Review>>:
    return products.stream()
        .collect(Collectors.toMap(
            Function.identity(),
            p -> byProductId.getOrDefault(p.getId(), List.of())
        ));
}
// Key difference:
// @SchemaMapping: (Product) → List<Review>   (called N times)
// @BatchMapping:  (List<Product>) → Map<Product, List<Review>>  (called once)
```

